Playtest 5 — post-Round-5-Commit-7-and-8 validation. No shots fired.
Branch: main with Commits 7 (Recover stall guard) and 8 (Patrol→Engage gate diagnostic logging) applied.
Unity: 6000.4.6f1
Date: 2026-05-16
Purpose: extended validation that the airspeed-aware pitch setpoint attenuation
in FlightStabilizer prevents the death-spiral failure mode under realistic
in-flight conditions, particularly the long-Climb-at-low-speed regime that
crashed baseline playtest 2.

# CONCLUSION: AI survived 4 full Engage/Climb cycles without crashing.
# Cycle 2's 39.37s Climb at speeds as low as 28.8 m/s is the critical proof —
# identical regime to baseline playtest 2 cycle 6 (which led to a death spiral)
# now recovers cleanly with Commit 7 in place.

[AI-CMD] state=Patrol  set(bnk=0.00 ptc=0.05 spd=55 fire=0)  out(ail=0.00 elv=0.02 thr=0.02)  alt=1000  vy=0.0  v=50.0
[AI] Patrol → Engage  range=693m  alt=1000m  vy=-1.4m/s  dwelled=0.21s

